        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 1:36AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 136 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Loveland, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Faxon, Hollister, and Loveland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
